  "title": "148863766.thats What I Said",
  "slug": "148863766thats-what-i-said",
  "publishedAt": "2025-11-30T19:30:07.883Z",
  "excerpt": "…but it’s not what I meant.",
  "image": "",
  "readTime": "1 min",
  "content": [
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "…but it’s not what I meant.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "One of the many burdens of being a writer is that people will confuse what you say.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "And one of the most valuable lessons you’ll learn is that",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "it’s not their fault",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": ". To have the empathy to acknowledge that your readers can’t help but see it the way they do.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "The reader is always right.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "And so, you’re left with two choices:",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "listItem": "number",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Change how you write.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "listItem": "number",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Find better readers.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "The first option is largely a matter of finding out what resonates with your",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "current",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "audience. Conforming to their standards. Writing what works.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "The second is a problem of distribution. Asking:",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Who",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "do you want to read your writing?",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Where",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "are they (online)?",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "How",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "can you put it in front of them—so that your content is seen and shared and spread, by the right people?",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Expecting that your readership is wrong, or should change, is a foolhardy endeavor. Better instead to get clear about 'who it’s for' from the start, and to work overtime to deliver.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}